Description: CVE-2026-5928 - Fix ungetwc operating on byte stream (BZ#33998)
 The _IO_wdefault_pbackfail function in libio/wgenops.c incorrectly uses
 fp->_IO_read_ptr (byte stream) instead of fp->_wide_data->_IO_read_ptr
 (wide stream) when comparing and decrementing the read pointer during
 wide character pushback. This causes a buffer under-read when ungetwc()
 is called, potentially leading to information disclosure or crashes when
 processing character encodings with overlaps between single-byte and
 multibyte representations. Bug introduced in glibc 2.1 (1999).
Origin: upstream, https://sourceware.org/pipermail/libc-alpha/2026-April/176798.html
Bug: https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33998
Bug-Debian: https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=1134544
Author: Rocket Ma <marocketbd@gmail.com>
Reviewed-by: Carlos O'Donell <carlos@redhat.com>
Last-Update: 2026-04-22

